<% content_for :title, "Whitmore Lake Public Schools School Policy Notices - FERPA, Safety, Compliance" %>
<% content_for :description, "Stay informed about Whitmore Lake Public Schools' policies, including FERPA rights, safety procedures, student privacy, and compliance with state and federal laws" %>

<div class="transparency_reporting">
    <div class="page_heading p-20" style="background-image: url('/assets/bg_2.png');">
        <h2 class="text-center text-white mb-0">News & Info</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="red_button_bar primary-bg py-3">
        <%= render "news_info_links_bar" %>
    </div>
    <div class="py-4_5">
        <div class="container">
            <h1><span>Whitmore Lake Public Schools</span><span class="text-black"> School Policy Notices</span></h1>
            <h2 class="text-black">Understanding WLPS School Policies & Legal Notices</h2>
            <p>
                Section 18 (2) of the Public Act 94 of 1979, The State School Aid Act, has been amended, which
                requires each school district and intermediate school district to post certain information on its
                website within 30 days after a board adopts it annual operating budget or any subsequent
                revision to that budget. The Annual Budget & Transparency Reporting is an opportunity to
                communicate with our community on how we utilize the resources that are provided to us.
            </p>
            <p>The following information is required to be posted on our website:</p>
            <ul class="mb-0" style="list-style-type: decimal;">
                <li>The annual operating budget and subsequent budget revisions.</li>
                <li>
                    Using data that has already been collected and submitted to the Michigan Department of
                    Education (MDE), a summary of district expenditures for the most recent fiscal year for which
                    they are available, expressed in the following two (2) pie charts which were provided for the
                    general fund of the district by the Center for Educational Performance and Information (CEPI):
                    <ul style="list-style-type: none; counter-reset: alpha-counter; padding-left: 0;">
                        <li class="alpha-counter">
                            A chart of personnel expenditures broken down into the following subcategories:
                            <ul style="list-style-type: none; counter-reset: decimal-counter; padding-left: 0;">
                                <li class="decimal-counter">Salaries and Wages</li>
                                <li class="decimal-counter">Employee benefit costs, including, but not limited to, medical, dental, vision, life, disability, and long term care benefits</li>
                                <li class="decimal-counter">Retirement benefits costs</li>
                                <li class="decimal-counter">All other personnel costs</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li class="alpha-counter">
                            A chart of all district expenditures, broken into the following subcategories:
                            <ul style="list-style-type: none; counter-reset: alpha-counter; padding-left: 0;">
                                <li class="decimal-counter">Instruction</li>
                                <li class="decimal-counter">Support Services</li>
                                <li class="decimal-counter">Business and administration</li>
                                <li class="decimal-counter">Operations and Maintenance</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    Links to all of the following:
                    <ul style="list-style-type: none; counter-reset: alpha-counter; padding-left: 0;">
                        <li class="alpha-counter">The current collective bargaining agreement for each bargaining unit</li>
                        <li class="alpha-counter">
                            Each health care benefit plan, including, but not limited to, medical, dental, vision, disability,
                            long-term care, or any other type of benefits that would constitute health care services, offered
                            to any bargaining unit or employee in the district
                        </li>
                        <li class="alpha-counter">The audit report of the audit conducted under subsection (4) for the most recent fiscal year for which it is available.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Bids required under section 5 of the public employee health benefits act, 2007 PA 106, MCL 124.75.</li>
                <li>The district's written policy governing procurement of supplies, materials, and equipment.</li>
                <li>The district's written policy establishing specific categories of reimbursable expenses, as described in section 1254(2) of the revised school code, MCL 380.1254.</li>
                <li>
                    Either the district's accounts payable check register for the most recent school fiscal year or a
                    statement of the total amount of expenses incurred by board members or employees of the
                    district that were reimbursed by the district for the most recent school fiscal year.
                </li>
                <li>
                    The total salary and a description and cost of each fringe benefit included in the
                    compensation package for the superintendent of the district and for each employee of the
                    district whose salary exceeds $100,000.00.
                </li>
                <li>The annual amount spent on dues paid to associations.</li>
                <li>The annual amount spent on lobbying or lobbying services. As used in this subdivision, “lobbying” means that term as defined in section 5 of 1978 PA 472, MCL 4.415.</li>
                <li>Any deficit elimination plan or enhanced deficit elimination plan the district was required to submit under this article.</li>
                <li>
                    Identification of all credit cards maintained by the district as district credit cards, the
                    identity of all individuals authorized to use each of those credit cards, the credit limit on each
                    credit card, and the dollar limit, if any, for each individual's authorized use of the credit card.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Costs incurred for each instance of out-of-state travel by the school administrator of the
                    district that is fully or partially paid for by the district and the details of each of those instances
                    of out-of-state travel, including at least identification of each individual on the trip, destination, and purpose.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="py-4_5" style="background-image: url('/assets/login_bg.png');">
        <div class="container">
            <% categories = {
                "Board Approved Budget" => [
                    "2023-24 Final Budget and 2024-25 Original Budget"
                ],
                "Personnel Expenditures" => [
                    "Personnel Expenditures 2023-24"
                ],
                "Current Operating Expenditures" => [
                    "Operating Expenditures 2023-24"
                ],
                "Current Bargaining Agreements" => [
                    "WLES Agreement 2022-2025",
                    "Office Assistants Agreement 2023-26",
                    "Paraprofessional Agreement 2023-26"
                ],
                "Employer-Sponsored Health Care Plans" => [
                    "MESSA Balance+ Summary of Benefits & Coverage",
                    "MESSA ABC Summary of Benefits & Coverage",
                    "MESSA LTD Plan Highlights - All Groups",
                    "MESSA Group Term Life Plan Highlights - All Groups",
                    "Dental Highlights Teacher - Administration",
                    "Vision Highlights Teacher - Administration",
                    "Dental Highlights Parapro - Office - Personnel - Transportation - Maintenance",
                    "Vision Highlights Parapro - Office - Personnel - Transportation - Maintenance"
                ],
                "Audited Financial Statements" => [
                    "2023-24 Audited Financial Statements",
                    "2022-23 Audited Financial Statements",
                    "2021-22 Audited Financial Statements",
                    "2020-21 Audited Financial Statements",
                    "2019-20 Audited Financial Statements",
                    "2018-19 Audited Financial Statements",
                    "2017-18 Audited Financial Statements",
                    "2016-17 Audited Financial Statements",
                    "2014-16 Audited Financial Statements",
                    "2014-15 Audited Financial Statements"
                ],
                "Medical Benefit Plan Bids" => [
                    "Health Plan Purchasing Consortium Agreement"
                ],
                "Procurement" => [
                    "Procurement"
                ],
                "Expense Reimbursement Policy" => [
                    "Expense Reimbursement Policy"
                ],
                "Accounts Payable Check Register" => [
                    "2023-24 Accounts Payable Payment Register"
                ],
                "Employee Compensation Information" => [
                    "Employee Compensation 2023"
                ],
                "District Paid Association Dues" => [
                    "District Paid Association Dues 2023-24"
                ],
                "District Paid Lobbying Costs" => [],
                "Approved Deficit Elimination Plan" => [],
                "District Credit Card Information" => [
                    "District Credit Card Information 2023-24"
                ],
                "District Paid Out-of-State Travel Information" => [],
                "MI School Data Portal" => [],
                "Educator Evaluation Postings and Assurances Documents for District-Use as required by Public Act 173 of 2015" => [
                    "Teacher Evaluation Posting and Assurances Tool",
                    "Teacher-Admin Evaluation Training Plan",
                    "Superintendent Evaluation Posting and Assurances Tool"
                ],
                "Extended COVID-19 Learning Plan" => [
                    "Extended COVId-19 Learning Plan",
                    "End of Year Extended COVID-19 Learning Plan",
                    "2021-2022 WLPS Extended COVID-19 Learning Goal Reporting 6.15.22",
                    "2022-2023 WLPS Extended COVID-19 Learning Goal Reporting"
                ],
                "Mitigating Learning Loss Prevention" => [
                    "WLPS 98c Board Presentation",
                    "98c Learning Loss Plan",
                    "Strategic 23g Budget",
                    "Strategic 23g Plan 3",
                    "Strategic 23g Plan Contact Information"
                ]
            } %>

            <% categories.each do |heading, titles| %>
                <h2 class="text-black mb-2 mt-3"><%= heading %></h2>
                <% if heading == "Medical Benefit Plan Bids" %>
                    <p>
                        Whitmore Lake Public Schools participates in the Washtenaw County Consortium for employee
                        medical insurance coverage for administrators, qualified non-union personnel, and all
                        bargaining groups. No bids have been requested.
                    </p>
                <% end %>
                <% if heading == "District Paid Lobbying Costs" %>
                    <p>Whitmore Lake Public Schools has no expenses related to district paid lobbying costs.</p>
                <% end %>
                <% if heading == "Approved Deficit Elimination Plan" %>
                    <p>Whitmore Lake Public Schools has not incurred a deficit.</p>
                <% end %>
                <% if heading == "District Paid Out-of-State Travel Information" %>
                    <p>Whitmore Lake Public Schools did not have any out-of-state travel.</p>
                <% end %>
                <% if heading == "MI School Data Portal" %>
                    <p>
                        Pursuant to the Best Practices Incentives Grant, as defined in MCL 388.1622f, the district
                        provides the following link to the MI School Data Portal which provides a dashboard
                        demonstrating the district's efforts to manage its finances responsibly.<br>
                        <a href="MISchoolData.org" class="text-red">www.MISchoolData.org</a>
                    </p>
                <% end %>
                <% @transparency_reporting_pdfs.each do |pdf_doc| %>
                    <% if pdf_doc.pdf.attached? && titles.include?(pdf_doc.title) %>
                        <% if pdf_doc.title == "Superintendent Evaluation Posting and Assurances Tool" %>
                            <p class="mb-0"><b>Administrator Evaluation Posting and Assurances Tool</b></p>
                        <% end %>
                        <%= link_to rails_blob_path(pdf_doc.pdf, disposition: "inline", only_path: true), target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "d-flex align-items-center color-normal mb-2 text-decoration-underline" do %>
                            <%= image_tag("pdf.png", alt: "View", class: "origin", style: "vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 4px;") %>
                            <%= pdf_doc.title %>
                        <% end %>
                    <% end %>
                <% end %>
            <% end %>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
